7: That quest took longer than I thought.
11: Quiet. This is bandit territory, Alk.
16:
Huh? How can you tell? It looks like
a plain old mountain trail to me.
20:
Look. There were people hiding among
the branches and in the thicket.
They may have been lying in wait for
adventurers. We should—
23:
Voices... It may be the sound of
an ambush!
31: Tch. Just a single brat, eh? That's no fun.
33:
Sometimes brats fetch a good price.
Hehe, just look at her fancy clothes.
35:
Maybe she's some noble's daughter.
Could ask for a hefty ransom?
37:
Then they'd hunt us down, you moron.
Better to tie up this loose end.
All nice and tidy, y'know?
41: Sigh. What a dearth of decorum.
47:
Despite your brutish exteriors, I wonder
if any of you are actually capable
fighters.
50:
You got a lotta lip on ya, girl. Can you
even imagine the situation you're in?
54:
Why yes, I can. Very soon, two brave
souls shall accost you from behind.
62:
Quite the heroic entrance.
But, of course, I need no saving.
68:
You wield a blade, correct?
Perhaps you should draw it?
73: So much for you. A pity, really.
84:
I most certainly did not!
I didn't even break flesh!
87:
You did all this with a nonlethal
technique? Impressive.
91:
Did you come to rescue me?
I thank you.
94:
But I would appreciate it more
if you could help me tie these fiends up.
110:
Thank you kindly. It'd have been a bit of
a struggle, dragging about these lugs
on my own.
117:
Yes. My frame is what it is,
unfortunately—but with time and luck,
I should grow taller!
121:
But you're still powerful enough to take
care of a pack of bandits.
That's awesome!
125:
Come to think of it, I don't believe we've
formally introduced ourselves yet.
129:
My name is Celtie Tris. I'm on a journey
from the Farlands to Palpebra.
132:
I'm Alk, and this is Light.
Nice to meet you.
136:
Well then, Sir Alk.
Forgive my impertinence, but could I
make a request of you?
139:
Uh, sure?
Not sure if you need my help but...
143:
Oh, it's just a simple request. I would like
a duel with you once we've descended
the mountain.
153: N-no, it's not that, I just—
158:
Then it's settled!
You have my every thanks!
171: Well! I simply can't leave you now.
178:
I never expected Sir Alk to collapse,
after only ten rounds.
181:
So we shall continue these proceedings
tomorrow!
186: Are you asking to sojourn here?
191:
Of course! I have yet to see the depths
of Sir Alk's swordsmanship, after all.
194:
You've taken quite a liking to Alk.
Do you find him to be a fitting rival?
198: A rival? No. He has no talent.
203:
That being said, no matter how
hopeless the battle, he never
surrenders. I find that intriguing.
209:
Very well. Then allow me to officially
welcome you to Starview Village, Celtie.
214: Thank you very much, Lady Stella!
220:
Do kindly get up, Sir Alk!
There's more dueling to be done!
